    "His ideas also encouraged the fascination with the study of African and South Seas art.": [],
    "The art historian <a href=\"/einsteinc\">Carl Einstein</a>, drew heavily upon Worringer's work for his own Negerplastik of 1915, as later did <a href=\"/readh\">Herbert Read</a>.": [],
    "Worringer's second work, <em>Formprobleme der Gotik</em>, developed the theme formulated in <em>Abstraktion</em> for one particular period, european medieval art.": [
        [
